    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offensive engine is anchored today by a high-upside core led by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84), **Kyle Tucker** (73.39), and **Gunnar Henderson** (73.38). **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against an hittable starter and carries significant momentum from an 8% boost due to elite BvP history. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** is poised for a massive outing; despite a 3.27 xERA opposing starter, he benefits from a 16% park factor jump and a 14% platoon edge, making him a cornerstone play. **Josh Lowe** (71.68) remains a high-priority start specifically for his stolen base potential; with a 5.60 xERA opponent and a slow delivery flag (+2% SB boost), he represents our best opportunity to capitalize on the league\u2019s scarcest category.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved **Nolan Schanuel**, who finished with a 58.92 score\u2014the highest of our bench\u2014falling just short of displacing **Andy Pages** (58.58). While **Nolan Schanuel** provided a stable floor, the optimizer prioritized the potential of **Andy Pages** in a matchup where we are hunting for ceiling rather than mere plate appearances. We are also closely monitoring **Liam Hicks** and **Drake Baldwin** at the catcher slots, both of whom are currently hovering in the 46-47 range; these are marginal starts necessitated by positional requirements, particularly with **Drake Baldwin** facing a difficult 2.71 xERA arm in Tarik Skubal, which heavily penalized his efficiency score.\n\nRisks today are dominated by the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters, which introduces volatility to our order-based bonuses. Specifically, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (49.20) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (50.71) are navigating significant dynamic platoon penalties (-15%), which have suppressed their scores toward the bottom of our starting threshold. Should any of these players be moved down in their respective batting orders, we will lose the projected order-position bumps that keep them afloat. We will also keep a close eye on **Marcell Ozuna**, who secured a 60.22 score largely due to favorable wind conditions (+5%); should that wind die down, his value will dip closer to the marginal range.",
